Description: SWELL simulates the daily dynamics of a remotely sensed vegetation index referred to a deciduous species. It uses photoperiod and temperature as key environmental cues, with species-specific photothermal requirements as input parameters. The core model is written in C#, and the package offers functions for automatic calibration (multi-start simplex) and validation
